# Festag — dark-mode CTAs

In **dark / OLED** auth and onboarding chrome, primary and ghost CTAs share one quiet slate fill until the form is ready.

## Idle (empty / invalid / not ready)

Both primary and ghost stay **darker / quieter**:

```css
background: rgba(186, 194, 210, 0.08); /* --festag-btn-dark-bg */
color: rgba(245, 245, 247, 0.88);
border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06); /* minimal white hairline */
```

Hover/active idle lifts only slightly (`0.16` / `0.22`).

## Ready (valid input → `--ready`)

Only the **primary** action flips to a **solid white** pill after successful input (e.g. valid email), Sana-style:

```css
background: #ffffff;
color: #1e1e20;
```

Hover `#fafafa`, active `#f4f4f5`. Ghost / secondary skip actions stay at idle density so the hierarchy is obvious.

## Tokens

Idle uses `--festag-btn-dark-*` from `components/auth/auth-chrome-tokens.ts`. Ready white may be hardcoded on `.al-btn-primary--ready` in dark (do not force near-white on idle).

## Do not

- Make idle primary and ready primary look the same
- Force `--ready` on empty invite / empty name fields / incomplete emails
- Give ghost the ready white fill (skip / secondary stays quiet)
- Reintroduce slate-only ready lift when the product asks for Sana white ready

See also `festag-light-mode-ctas.mdc` (light stays white fills) and `festag-auth-no-field-borders.mdc`.
